definition.value: A member of the class of allenes that is cyclohexane substituted by 3-oxobut-1-en-1-ylidene, methyl, hydroxy, hydroxy, methyl and methyl groups at positions 1, 2, 2, 4, 6 and 6, respectively (the 2R,3R,4S-stereoisomer). It is isolated from the grasshopper, Romalea microptera.
A nickel-iron-sulfur cluster in which the nickel and iron atoms are linked by bridging sulfur atoms with the ratio Ni:Fe:S = 1:4:5.

A member of the class of benzimidazoles that is 1H-benzimidazole substituted by (4-benzylpiperidin-1-yl)methyl and (methylsulfonyl)amino groups at positions 2 and 6, respectively. It is a potent antagonist of the GluN2B subunit of the N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor.

A member of the class of benzimidazoles that is 1H-benzimidazole substituted by 4-phenoxybenzyl and (methylsulfonyl)amino groups at positions 2 and 6, respectively. It is a potent antagonist of the GluN2B subunit of the N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor.
A pentasaccharide derivative that comprises the distal pentasaccharide of the oligosaccharide segment of Bordetella pertussis strain 186 lipooligosaccharide.
A twelve-residue oligosaccharide derivative that comprises the core oligosaccharide and distal trisaccharide of the oligosaccharide segment of Bordetella pertussis strain 186 lipooligosaccharide.
A cyclopropylcarboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of cyclopropanecarboxylic acid with the amino group of 3,7-dimethylocta-2,6-dien-1-amine.
An oxo dicarboxylic acid dianion that is the conjugate base of 2-oxosuberic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the two carboxy groups. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An N-alkylpiperazine that consists of piperazine bearing 2-(benzhydryloxy)ethyl and 2-(4-azido-3-iodophenyl)ethyl groups at positions 1 and 4 respectively.

A member of the class of piperidines that is piperidine substituted by (4-azidophenyl)methyl and 2-(diphenylmethoxy)ethyl groups at positions 1 and 4, respectively. It binds to the dopamine transporter ligand binding site.
This is a tropane ring containing compound that binds the dopamine transporter ligand binding site.
A sesterterpene that is produced by several fungal chimeric terpene synthases (PTTS009, PTTS037 and PTTS054).
A sesterterpene that is produced by a fungal chimeric terpene synthase, PTTS010.
A tricyclic diterpene that was initially produced by a chimeric terpene synthase gene found in the fungus Emericella variecolor which was heterologously expressed in Aspergillus oryzae.
A sesterterpene.
A benzophenanthridine alkaloid that is dihydrosanguinarine bearing a methoxy substituent at position 10.

A sesterterpene that is produced by the fungal chimeric terpene synthase, PTTS036.
A sesterterpene.
A sesterterpene.
A sesterterpene that is produced by a fungal chimeric terpene synthase, PTTS051.
A diterpene.
A sesterterpene.
A diterpenoid that is produced by the fungal chimeric terpene synthases, PTTS087 and PTTS136.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxy groups of any omega-carboxy-(fatty acyl)-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A diterpene.
The primary alcohol that is the simplest aliphatic alcohol, comprising a methyl and an alcohol group.
A sesterterpene that is produced by the fungal chimeric terpene synthase, PTTS125.
A sesterterpene that is produced by the fungal chimeric terpene synthase, PTTS125.
An acyclic carotene that is lycopene having a cis-double bond at position 5.
An acyclic carotene that is lycopene having a cis-double bond at position 13.
An oxo dicarboxylic acid that is adipic acid substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and chloro groups at positions 2 and 4.
